### ISSUE #8: PunctuationQueue Synchronized on Collection

**File:** `/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/PunctuationQueue.java`

**Lock Details:**
- Line 27: `private final PriorityQueue<PunctuationSchedule> pq = new PriorityQueue<>();`
- Synchronized blocks at lines 30, 37, 46, 74

**Code (Lines 45-68):**
```java
boolean maybePunctuate(final long timestamp, final PunctuationType type, ...) {
    synchronized (pq) {
        boolean punctuated = false;
        PunctuationSchedule top = pq.peek();
        while (top != null && top.timestamp <= timestamp) {
            final PunctuationSchedule sched = top;
            pq.poll();
            if (!sched.isCancelled()) {
                processorNodePunctuator.punctuate(sched.node(), timestamp, type, sched.punctuator());  // EXTERNAL CALL
                if (!sched.isCancelled()) {
                    pq.add(sched.next(timestamp));
                }
                punctuated = true;
            }
            top = pq.peek();
        }
        return punctuated;
    }
}
```

**Hazard:** Calling `processorNodePunctuator.punctuate()` while holding lock on `pq` can lead to:
1. Nested lock acquisition if punctuator accesses shared state protected by different locks
2. Long-held locks while doing processing work
3. Callback-induced reentrancy issues

